relationships.description: The wet well control system contains a pump control unit
The system monitors and switches multiple submersible pumps
The pump control unit controls multiple submersible pumps
Each submersible pump is equipped with one moisture sensor
Level switches indicate when pumps should be started
Float switches set states for pump activation or alarm
The system has one control display panel for depth readout
Monitors the access door for prohibited entry
Indicator lights for various pump and alarm states

requirement_issues.requirement_text: The design of the wet well control system shall provide for the safety and protection of pumping station operators, maintenance personnel, and the public from hazards that may result from its operation.

issues.description: The term 'safety and protection' is high-level and does not specify which hazards to address or how to measure safety outcomes.
issues.suggested_fix: Specify the types of hazards (e.g., electrical shock, flooding) and the safety measures (e.g., interlocks, alarms, physical barriers) to be provided.

issues.description: It is unclear how compliance with 'provide for the safety and protection' can be verified or tested.
issues.suggested_fix: Define measurable safety requirements and acceptance criteria (e.g., response time for alarms, fail-safe modes).

requirement_issues.requirement_text: The control system shall be responsible for monitoring and reporting the level of liquid in the wet well.

issues.description: The requirement does not specify measurement accuracy, sampling frequency, data format, or reporting destination.
issues.suggested_fix: Specify the required accuracy (±x inches), sampling interval (e.g., every 5 seconds), and how and where the data is reported (e.g., display panel, SCADA).

requirement_issues.requirement_text: The control system shall be responsible for monitoring and reporting the state of each pump and whether it is currently running or not.

issues.description: The requirement uses both 'state of each pump' and 'whether it is currently running', which are redundant.
issues.suggested_fix: Consolidate terminology to a single phrase such as 'running state' or 'operational state'.

requirement_issues.requirement_text: The control system shall be responsible for activating a visual and audible alarm when a hazardous condition exists.

issues.description: The term 'hazardous condition' is not defined, making it unclear when alarms should activate.
issues.suggested_fix: List specific hazardous conditions (e.g., high water level, seal failure, unauthorized entry) that should trigger alarms.

requirement_issues.requirement_text: The control system shall be responsible for switching each submersible pump on or off in a timely fashion depending on the level of liquid within the wet well.

issues.description: The phrase 'timely fashion' is vague and does not specify response time requirements.
issues.suggested_fix: Define the maximum allowable delay between level threshold detection and pump activation/deactivation (e.g., <5 seconds).

requirement_issues.requirement_text: The wet well control system shall provide automated operation.

issues.description: This requirement is duplicated by REQ-017, leading to confusion about its unique purpose.
issues.suggested_fix: Merge REQ-006 and REQ-017 into a single unambiguous requirement specifying automated operation modes.

requirement_issues.requirement_text: The wet well control system shall provide local manual override operation.

issues.description: REQ-016 overlaps with this requirement, causing duplicate functionality descriptions.
issues.suggested_fix: Consolidate REQ-007 and REQ-016 into one clear requirement for manual override.

requirement_issues.requirement_text: The wet well control system shall provide local observational operation.

issues.description: The term 'observational operation' is not defined; unclear what operators can observe and how.
issues.suggested_fix: Describe what information is available in observational mode (e.g., current level, pump status) and what controls are disabled.

requirement_issues.requirement_text: The wet well control system shall start the pump motors to prevent the wet well from running over and stop the pump motors before the wet well runs dry.

issues.description: Threshold levels for starting/stopping pumps are not specified here, though later requirements define them.
issues.suggested_fix: Reference the depth thresholds from REQ-044 through REQ-046 to clarify activation points.

requirement_issues.requirement_text: The wet well control system shall monitor the pumping site for unauthorized entry or trespass.

issues.description: The requirement does not specify the detection mechanism (e.g., door sensor, motion detector).
issues.suggested_fix: Specify the sensor type or method to detect unauthorized entry (e.g., AccessDoor circuit sensor).

requirement_issues.requirement_text: The wet well control system shall monitor the environmental conditions within the wet well.

issues.description: The phrase 'environmental conditions' is too broad and does not identify which parameters to monitor (e.g., temperature, gas levels).
issues.suggested_fix: List the specific environmental parameters to be monitored (e.g., internal temperature, humidity, hazardous gases).

requirement_issues.requirement_text: The wet well control system shall monitor the physical condition of each pump for the existence of moisture and excessive temperatures.

issues.description: Temperature thresholds and moisture detection methods are not defined, making validation impossible.
issues.suggested_fix: Define the maximum allowable temperature and specify the type and placement of moisture sensors.

requirement_issues.requirement_text: The wet well control system shall display real time and historical operational parameters.

issues.description: The term 'operational parameters' is vague; it is unclear which parameters must be displayed.
issues.suggested_fix: Specify the list of parameters (e.g., liquid level, pump run time, alarm history) to be shown.

requirement_issues.requirement_text: The wet well control system shall provide an alarm feature.

issues.description: This overlaps with more detailed alarm requirements (REQ-004, REQ-025, REQ-032) without adding clarity.
issues.suggested_fix: Remove or merge into more specific alarm requirements to avoid redundancy.

requirement_issues.requirement_text: The wet well control system shall provide a manual override of the site.

issues.description: Duplicate of REQ-007 describing manual override capability.
issues.suggested_fix: Merge with REQ-007 to consolidate manual override functionality.

requirement_issues.requirement_text: The wet well control system shall provide automated operation of the site.

issues.description: Duplicate of REQ-006 describing automated operation.
issues.suggested_fix: Merge with REQ-006 to consolidate automated operation requirement.

requirement_issues.requirement_text: Should a seal failure be detected, the pump shall be turned off and alarm state set.

issues.description: Does not specify which system component (WWCS or PCU) is responsible for turning off the pump and setting the alarm.
issues.suggested_fix: Clarify whether the WetWellControlSystem or the PumpControlUnit performs shutdown and alarm activation.

requirement_issues.requirement_text: The pump control unit shall start the submersible pump motors to prevent the wet well from running over and stop the pump motors before the wet well runs dry.

issues.description: This requirement duplicates functionality described in REQ-009 at a different component level.
issues.suggested_fix: Ensure clear separation of responsibilities or collapse into a single pump control requirement.

requirement_issues.requirement_text: The pump control unit shall keep track of whether or not each motor is running.

issues.description: Duplicate of REQ-010 monitoring requirement at the pump control unit level.
issues.suggested_fix: Reference the existing motor running state requirement centrally or remove redundancy.

requirement_issues.requirement_text: An alarm state shall be set when the high water level is reached.

issues.description: Overlap with REQ-004 and PCU alarm requirements; unclear which module sets the alarm state.
issues.suggested_fix: Specify which control unit (WWCS or PCU) is responsible for detecting high water and setting the alarm.

requirement_issues.requirement_text: The starting and stopping of the pump motors shall be done in manner that equalizes the run times on the motors.

issues.description: Overlaps with REQ-018 regarding run time equalization; could be consolidated.
issues.suggested_fix: Merge with REQ-018 to avoid repeating the equalization requirement.

requirement_issues.requirement_text: The pump control unit shall be responsible for monitoring the pumping site.

issues.description: It is not clear what aspects of the pumping site should be monitored (e.g., entry, vibration).
issues.suggested_fix: Define specific monitoring targets such as access doors, vibration, or environmental sensors.

requirement_issues.requirement_text: The pump control unit shall be responsible for providing the alarm feature.

issues.description: Duplicates alarm functionality described in REQ-004 and REQ-015 at this component level without detail.
issues.suggested_fix: Consolidate into one alarm requirement or specify distinct alarm behaviors for the PCU.

requirement_issues.requirement_text: Monitor and detect prohibited entry to the wet well through the access door by way of broken electrical circuit. Both audible and visible alarms shall be activated.

issues.description: REQ-036 repeats this requirement, leading to redundancy.
issues.suggested_fix: Remove REQ-036 and retain a single entry for prohibited access detection.

requirement_issues.requirement_text: Monitor and detect occurrence of a pump motor seal leak. If a leak has been detected, both an audible and visible alarm should be activated.

issues.description: Similar to REQ-028 (excess moisture notification), creating confusion over which requirement drives leak detection versus moisture alarms.
issues.suggested_fix: Clarify separation of seal leak detection (REQ-034) from general moisture detection (REQ-028) or merge if they refer to the same sensor.

requirement_issues.requirement_text: Monitor and detect prohibited entry by way of a broken electrical circuit. Both audible and visible alarms shall be activated.

issues.description: Duplicate of REQ-033 with slightly different wording.
issues.suggested_fix: Merge or remove redundant requirement to maintain a single definition.

requirement_issues.requirement_text: The pump control unit shall be responsible for displaying real time and historical operational parameters.

issues.description: Overlaps with REQ-014 and REQ-031, causing redundant display requirements.
issues.suggested_fix: Reference the central display requirement or merge into one comprehensive display requirement.

requirement_issues.requirement_text: When the depth of liquid is equal to or greater than the lead pump depth, the float switch shall set a state which causes the first pump to turn on.

issues.description: Lead pump depth threshold is not quantified in this requirement.
issues.suggested_fix: Provide the numerical depth value or reference a specification document for the lead pump depth setting.

requirement_issues.requirement_text: When the depth of liquid is equal to or greater than the lag pump depth, the float switch shall set a state which causes the second pump to turn on.

issues.description: Lag pump depth threshold is not specified.
issues.suggested_fix: Specify the lag pump depth value or reference a configuration parameter.

requirement_issues.requirement_text: When the depth of liquid is equal to or greater than the allowable high liquid depth, the float switch shall set an alarm state.

issues.description: Allowable high liquid depth threshold is not defined.
issues.suggested_fix: Define the high liquid depth value or reference a configuration document for this threshold.

domain_model_issues.description: No class for continuous measurement of liquid level exists, yet requirements call for monitoring and reporting liquid level (REQ-002, REQ-014) and thresholds for pump control (REQ-044–REQ-046).
domain_model_issues.suggested_fix: Introduce a LiquidLevelSensor class with attributes such as currentLevel (float) and methods to sample and report level.

domain_model_issues.description: Requirements mandate monitoring excessive temperatures (REQ-013, REQ-029), but no temperature sensor class is present.
domain_model_issues.suggested_fix: Add a TemperatureSensor class associated with SubmersiblePump to monitor motor temperature.

domain_model_issues.description: Environment monitoring within the wet well (REQ-012) is required but no corresponding sensor class exists.
domain_model_issues.suggested_fix: Create an EnvironmentalSensor class for parameters like humidity, gas concentration, and temperature.

domain_model_issues.description: The IndicatorLight class lacks a distinguishing attribute to specify which condition (pump running, seal failure, overheat, high level) it represents.
domain_model_issues.suggested_fix: Add a 'type' or 'condition' attribute (enumeration) to IndicatorLight to differentiate light purposes.

domain_model_issues.description: FloatSwitch only has a single 'state' attribute; it needs specific threshold values for lead pump, lag pump, and high alarm depths (REQ-044, REQ-045, REQ-046).
domain_model_issues.suggested_fix: Add attributes such as leadPumpDepth (float), lagPumpDepth (float), and highLiquidDepth (float).

domain_model_issues.description: ControlDisplayPanel lacks a method to display real time and historical operational parameters as required by REQ-014, REQ-031, REQ-037.
domain_model_issues.suggested_fix: Add a displayOperationalParameters(params: List<Parameter>) method to ControlDisplayPanel.

domain_model_issues.description: Duplicated functionality: automatedOperation overlaps with provideAutomatedOperation; leads to confusion.
domain_model_issues.suggested_fix: Remove the redundant automatedOperation method and use provideAutomatedOperation consistently.

domain_model_issues.description: Both WetWellControlSystem and PumpControlUnit implement keepTrackMotorRunning; responsibility should be centralized.
domain_model_issues.suggested_fix: Assign motor running state tracking exclusively to PumpControlUnit and remove from WetWellControlSystem.

domain_model_issues.description: Alarm activation methods are scattered across WetWellControlSystem (activateVisualAlarm/activateAudibleAlarm) and PumpControlUnit (setAlarmState/provideAlarmFeature).
domain_model_issues.suggested_fix: Consolidate alarm logic into a dedicated AlarmManager component or clearly define which class handles which alarms.

domain_model_issues.description: WetWellControlSystem has methods to activate audible alarms but no association with the Buzzer class.
domain_model_issues.suggested_fix: Add a composition relationship from WetWellControlSystem to Buzzer to allow alarm activation.

domain_model_issues.description: WetWellControlSystem defines monitorUnauthorizedEntry but has no link to AccessDoor.
domain_model_issues.suggested_fix: Add an association from WetWellControlSystem to AccessDoor or delegate monitoring to PumpControlUnit with clear interface.

domain_model_issues.description: Requirements differentiate external seal failure (MoistureSensor) and pump motor moisture (REQ-028); a separate sensor class may be needed.
domain_model_issues.suggested_fix: Introduce a MotorMoistureSensor class to represent internal motor moisture detection.

missing_requirements.description: No requirement specifies how operators select or view the current operation mode (automated, local manual override, local observational).
missing_requirements.suggested_requirement: The system shall provide an interface on the control display panel to allow authorized personnel to select between automated, local manual override, and local observational operation modes, and shall display the currently active mode at all times.
missing_requirements.rationale: REQ-006/REQ-017/REQ-007/REQ-008 define the modes but do not describe how an operator switches modes or sees which mode is active. A concrete UI requirement is needed to implement these methods.

missing_requirements.description: The float switch depth thresholds (lead pump activation, lag pump activation, and high-liquid alarm depth) are defined in REQ-044/045/046 but are fixed and not configurable.
missing_requirements.suggested_requirement: The system shall allow authorized personnel to configure and persistently store the float switch depth thresholds for lead pump activation depth, lag pump activation depth, and allowable high liquid depth via the control display panel or remote interface.
missing_requirements.rationale: Different installations require different setpoints; without a configure function the system cannot be adapted to site-specific conditions.

missing_requirements.description: REQ-013 and REQ-029 mandate detection of excessive temperatures but do not specify use of a temperature sensor or sampling interval.
missing_requirements.suggested_requirement: Each submersible pump motor shall be equipped with a temperature sensor that measures motor temperature at intervals no greater than 30 seconds and notifies the pump control unit when the temperature exceeds a configurable threshold.
missing_requirements.rationale: Monitoring overheating requires a concrete sensor and sampling requirements; without this, the overheat detection logic has no input.

missing_requirements.description: No requirement specifies how alarms may be acknowledged or silenced once activated.
missing_requirements.suggested_requirement: The system shall provide an alarm acknowledgment function that allows authorized operators to acknowledge active alarms, silencing the audible buzzer and latching the visual alarm state until the hazardous condition is resolved.
missing_requirements.rationale: Operators must confirm alarm receipt to avoid alarm fatigue and to support orderly alarm management; without an acknowledge function alarms cannot be managed.

missing_requirements.description: There are no requirements for sensor health or communication failure detection (self-diagnostics).
missing_requirements.suggested_requirement: The system shall perform self-diagnostic checks on all connected sensors (level switches, float switches, moisture sensors, temperature sensors, and access door circuits) at startup and at least every 5 minutes, and shall generate an alarm if any sensor fails to respond, reports values out of its normal range, or is disconnected.
missing_requirements.rationale: Sensor failures or disconnections could lead to undetected dangerous conditions; regular self-diagnostics ensure system integrity.

missing_requirements.description: Manual override and configuration functions are not protected by authentication or access control.
missing_requirements.suggested_requirement: The system shall require user authentication (e.g., username/password or key card) before allowing access to manual override operations or to any configuration settings on the control display panel.
missing_requirements.rationale: Unauthorized access to override or configuration could compromise safety or system integrity; security controls are essential.

missing_requirements.description: No requirement exists for remote monitoring or control via standard industrial protocols (SCADA).
missing_requirements.suggested_requirement: The system shall provide a SCADA-compatible communication interface (e.g., Modbus/TCP or DNP3) to enable remote monitoring of liquid levels, pump states, alarms, and to permit remote start/stop commands, supporting at least one concurrent client.
missing_requirements.rationale: Industrial pumping stations are typically integrated into a supervisory control network; without a remote interface the system cannot report to or be managed by central operations.

missing_requirements.description: No performance or real-time response requirements are defined for critical actions (pump start/stop, alarm activation).
missing_requirements.suggested_requirement: The system shall initiate any pump start or stop operation and activate any visual or audible alarm within 2 seconds of detecting the corresponding triggering condition.
missing_requirements.rationale: Delayed responses to high water levels or hazardous conditions can lead to overflows or damage; a quantified response time is essential for safety.

missing_requirements.description: System behavior on primary power loss is not defined.
missing_requirements.suggested_requirement: The system shall detect a loss of primary power, transition to backup power if available, stop all pump operations, activate both audible and visual alarms, and log the power loss event.
missing_requirements.rationale: Power outages can leave the wet well unmonitored and unsafe; the system must fail to a safe state and notify operators.

missing_requirements.description: Log retention period and export capabilities are not specified for recorded operational parameters.
missing_requirements.suggested_requirement: The system shall timestamp and log all operational events and sensor readings in non-volatile memory, retain logs for a minimum of 12 months, and provide a mechanism to export logs in CSV format via the control display panel or remote interface.
missing_requirements.rationale: Historical data is required for compliance audits, troubleshooting, and maintenance planning; without defined retention and export functions, this information cannot be effectively managed.

requirement_completeness.requirement_text: The design of the wet well control system shall provide for the safety and protection of pumping station operators, maintenance personnel, and the public from hazards that may result from its operation.
requirement_completeness.suggested_improvement: 'REQ-001 (Priority: High; Version: 1.0; Status: Draft; Rationale: Ensure operator safety; Source: Safety Officer; Dependencies: REQ-004; Type: Functional) The WetWellControlSystem shall protect pumping station operators, maintenance personnel, and the public from operational hazards. Acceptance Criteria: System triggers visual and audible alarms within 100 ms of hazard detection and logs hazard events.'
requirement_completeness.rationale: Including priority, rationale, source, version, status, dependencies, and acceptance criteria improves testability, traceability, and clarity.

requirement_completeness.requirement_text: The control system shall be responsible for monitoring and reporting the level of liquid in the wet well.
requirement_completeness.suggested_improvement: 'REQ-002 (Priority: High; Version: 1.0; Status: Draft; Rationale: Level monitoring critical for pump control; Source: Operations Team; Dependencies: REQ-005; Type: Functional) The WetWellControlSystem shall continuously monitor the liquid level in the wet well and report measurements to the SCADA system every second. Acceptance Criteria: Level readings updated every second with accuracy ±0.1 ft.'
requirement_completeness.rationale: Adding priority, rationale, source, version, status, dependencies, and acceptance criteria makes the requirement explicit and verifiable.

requirement_completeness.requirement_text: The control system shall be responsible for monitoring and reporting the state of each pump and whether it is currently running or not.
requirement_completeness.suggested_improvement: 'REQ-003 (Priority: High; Version: 1.0; Status: Draft; Rationale: Pump state monitoring ensures proper operation; Source: Operations Team; Dependencies: REQ-002; Type: Functional) The WetWellControlSystem shall monitor each pump's running state and report it to the control panel every 2 seconds. Acceptance Criteria: Pump state updates occur within 2 s and are logged with timestamp.'
requirement_completeness.rationale: Explicit acceptance criteria and metadata enable verification and traceability.

requirement_completeness.requirement_text: The control system shall be responsible for activating a visual and audible alarm when a hazardous condition exists.
requirement_completeness.suggested_improvement: 'REQ-004 (Priority: High; Version: 1.0; Status: Draft; Rationale: Alarm activation critical for safety; Source: Safety Officer; Dependencies: REQ-001; Type: Functional) The WetWellControlSystem shall activate a visual indicator and audible buzzer within 500 ms of detecting a hazardous condition. Acceptance Criteria: Both alarms activate within 500 ms and remain active until the condition clears.'
requirement_completeness.rationale: Defining thresholds and timing ensures alarm behavior is testable.

requirement_completeness.requirement_text: The control system shall be responsible for switching each submersible pump on or off in a timely fashion depending on the level of liquid within the wet well.
requirement_completeness.suggested_improvement: 'REQ-005 (Priority: High; Version: 1.0; Status: Draft; Rationale: Timely pump control prevents overflow or dry-run; Source: Design Engineer; Dependencies: REQ-002; Type: Functional) The WetWellControlSystem shall switch each submersible pump on or off within 1 s of the liquid level crossing predefined thresholds. Acceptance Criteria: Pump switch commands executed within 1 s of threshold crossing and actions are logged.'
requirement_completeness.rationale: Specifying timing and thresholds makes the requirement measurable.

requirement_completeness.requirement_text: The wet well control system shall provide automated operation.
requirement_completeness.suggested_improvement: 'REQ-006 (Priority: Medium; Version: 1.0; Status: Draft; Rationale: Automate routine operations to reduce manual work; Source: Automation Team; Dependencies: None; Type: Functional) The WetWellControlSystem shall provide an automated operation mode under normal conditions. Acceptance Criteria: System enters automated mode at startup and performs pump control without manual input.'
requirement_completeness.rationale: Clarifying mode behavior and acceptance criteria ensures automation is verifiable.

requirement_completeness.requirement_text: The wet well control system shall provide local manual override operation.
requirement_completeness.suggested_improvement: 'REQ-007 (Priority: Medium; Version: 1.0; Status: Draft; Rationale: Allow manual control during maintenance; Source: Maintenance Team; Dependencies: None; Type: Functional) The WetWellControlSystem shall provide a local manual override mode that allows operators to manually start and stop pumps. Acceptance Criteria: Manual commands override automation within 1 s and are logged.'
requirement_completeness.rationale: Defining override timing and logging makes the feature testable.

requirement_completeness.requirement_text: The wet well control system shall provide local observational operation.
requirement_completeness.suggested_improvement: 'REQ-008 (Priority: Low; Version: 1.0; Status: Draft; Rationale: Observation mode for diagnostics; Source: Maintenance Team; Dependencies: None; Type: Functional) The WetWellControlSystem shall provide a local observational mode that displays system status without issuing control commands. requirement_completeness.rationale: Specifying mode behavior and acceptance criteria ensures clarity.

requirement_completeness.requirement_text: The wet well control system shall start the pump motors to prevent the wet well from running over and stop the pump motors before the wet well runs dry.
requirement_completeness.suggested_improvement: 'REQ-009 (Priority: High; Version: 1.0; Status: Draft; Rationale: Prevent overflow and dry-run to protect equipment; Source: Design Engineer; Dependencies: REQ-002, REQ-005; Type: Functional) The WetWellControlSystem shall start pump motors when the high-level threshold is reached and stop motors when the low-level threshold is reached. Acceptance Criteria: Pump start/stop occurs within 500 ms of threshold crossing.'
requirement_completeness.rationale: Providing explicit thresholds and timing makes the requirement measurable.

requirement_completeness.requirement_text: The wet well control system shall keep track of whether or not each motor is running.
requirement_completeness.suggested_improvement: 'REQ-010 (Priority: Low; Version: 1.0; Status: Draft; Rationale: Track motor running state for diagnostics; Source: Maintenance Team; Dependencies: REQ-003; Type: Functional) The WetWellControlSystem shall track each motor's running state and log the status every second. Acceptance Criteria: Motor running state is logged every second with timestamp accuracy ±100 ms.'
requirement_completeness.rationale: Adding logging frequency and timestamp precision ensures verifiability.

requirement_completeness.requirement_text: The wet well control system shall monitor the pumping site for unauthorized entry or trespass.

Acceptance Criteria: Unauthorized entry detection triggers alarms within 1 s and logs the event.'
requirement_completeness.rationale: Specifying response time and logging makes security monitoring testable.

requirement_completeness.requirement_text: The wet well control system shall monitor the environmental conditions within the wet well.

requirement_completeness.requirement_text: The wet well control system shall monitor the physical condition of each pump for the existence of moisture and excessive temperatures.

requirement_completeness.requirement_text: The wet well control system shall display real time and historical operational parameters.

requirement_completeness.requirement_text: The wet well control system shall provide an alarm feature.

requirement_completeness.requirement_text: The wet well control system shall provide a manual override of the site.

requirement_completeness.rationale: Defining override effect and timing makes requirement measurable.

requirement_completeness.requirement_text: The wet well control system shall provide automated operation of the site.
requirement_completeness.suggested_improvement: 'REQ-017 (Priority: Medium; Version: 1.0; Status: Draft; Rationale: Full automation for normal operations; Source: Automation Team; Dependencies: REQ-006; Type: Functional) The WetWellControlSystem shall manage pump start/stop logic automatically under normal conditions. requirement_completeness.rationale: Clarifying scope and acceptance criteria ensures testable automation.

requirement_completeness.requirement_text: The wet well control system shall equalize the run time between the pumps.

requirement_completeness.requirement_text: Each submersible pump shall be equipped with a moisture sensor that detects the occurrence of an external pump seal failure.

requirement_completeness.rationale: Adding timing and reporting criteria improves testability.

requirement_completeness.requirement_text: Should a seal failure be detected, the pump shall be turned off and alarm state set.
requirement_completeness.suggested_improvement: 'REQ-020 (Priority: High; Version: 1.0; Status: Draft; Rationale: Rapid response to seal failure reduces risk; Source: Engineering Team; Dependencies: REQ-019; Type: Functional) When a seal failure is detected, the system shall turn off the affected pump and set the alarm state. requirement_completeness.rationale: Specifying response time and dependencies ensures clarity.

requirement_completeness.requirement_text: The pump control unit shall start the submersible pump motors to prevent the wet well from running over and stop the pump motors before the wet well runs dry.
requirement_completeness.suggested_improvement: 'REQ-021 (Priority: High; Version: 1.0; Status: Draft; Rationale: Prevent overflow/dry-run at pump unit level; Source: Design Engineer; Dependencies: REQ-009; Type: Functional) The PumpControlUnit shall start submersible pump motors when the high-level threshold is reached and stop them before low-level threshold is reached. requirement_completeness.rationale: Aligning unit-level behavior with system-level thresholds ensures consistency.

requirement_completeness.requirement_text: The pump control unit shall keep track of whether or not each motor is running.
requirement_completeness.suggested_improvement: 'REQ-022 (Priority: Low; Version: 1.0; Status: Draft; Rationale: Track motor run state in PumpControlUnit; Source: Maintenance Team; Dependencies: REQ-021; Type: Functional) The PumpControlUnit shall track each motor's running state and log it every second. requirement_completeness.requirement_text: The pump control unit shall keep track of whether or not each motor is available to run.

requirement_completeness.requirement_text: If a pump motor is not available to run and a request has been made for the pump motor to start, an alternative motor shall be started in its place.

requirement_completeness.rationale: Specifying timing makes redundancy behavior testable.

requirement_completeness.requirement_text: An alarm state shall be set when the high water level is reached.

requirement_completeness.rationale: Adding timing and activation criteria ensures requirement is measurable.

requirement_completeness.requirement_text: The starting and stopping of the pump motors shall be done in manner that equalizes the run times on the motors.

requirement_completeness.rationale: Quantifying the equalization metric makes the requirement testable.

requirement_completeness.requirement_text: Level switches shall be used to indicate when pump motors should be started.

requirement_completeness.rationale: Defining signal timing and thresholds ensures clear behavior.

requirement_completeness.requirement_text: The pump control unit shall be notified if excess moisture is detected in a pump motor.

requirement_completeness.requirement_text: The pump control unit shall be responsible for monitoring the pumping site.

requirement_completeness.requirement_text: The pump control unit shall be responsible for recording real time and historical operational parameters.

requirement_completeness.requirement_text: The pump control unit shall be responsible for providing the alarm feature.

requirement_completeness.requirement_text: Monitor and detect prohibited entry to the wet well through the access door by way of broken electrical circuit. Both audible and visible alarms shall be activated.

requirement_completeness.requirement_text: Monitor and detect prohibited entry by way of a broken electrical circuit. Both audible and visible alarms shall be activated.

requirement_completeness.requirement_text: The pump control unit shall be responsible for displaying real time and historical operational parameters.
